        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-11 19:31:19.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-15 05:44:35.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2150 ost: ost_brw_read() to ptlrpc_free_bulk_nopin()",
        "message": "LU-2150 ost: ost_brw_read() to ptlrpc_free_bulk_nopin()\n\nsince a643e38 (LU-2089) OST do not pin pages involved in\nBULKs: this is done to prevent get/put on the pages which\nwere allocated as part of order N (>1) allocation with 0\nrefcounter. get/put on such a page leads to warning from\nthe kernel. in the original patch one code path was not\nfixed, so this patch completes the change.\n\nalso, to prevent confusion, the patch removes couple macros:\nptlrpc_free_bulk() and ptlrpc_prep_bulk_page(). so now the\ncaller should specify whether ptlrpc should reference pages\nor not.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I8cf5f334e8f7edab0ad37678e1e8af18904a0be6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
